monaco.Uri.description:
Uniform Resource Identifier (Uri) http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986.
This class is a simple parser which creates the basic component parts
(http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-3) with minimal validation
and encoding.

```txt
      foo://example.com:8042/over/there?name=ferret#nose
      \_/   \______________/\_________/ \_________/ \__/
       |           |            |            |        |
    scheme     authority       path        query   fragment
       |   _____________________|__
      / \ /                        \
      urn:example:animal:ferret:nose
```

authority.description:
authority is the 'www.msft.com' part of 'http://www.msft.com/some/path?query#fragment'.
The part between the first double slashes and the next slash.
authority.title: authority

fsPath.description:
Returns a string representing the corresponding file system path of this Uri.
Will handle UNC paths, normalizes windows drive letters to lower-case, and uses the
platform specific path separator.

* Will *not* validate the path for invalid characters and semantics.
* Will *not* look at the scheme of this Uri.
* The result shall *not* be used for display purposes but for accessing a file on disk.


The *difference* to `Uri#path` is the use of the platform specific separator and the handling
of UNC paths. See the below sample of a file-uri with an authority (UNC path).

```ts
 const u = Uri.parse('file://server/c$/folder/file.txt')
 u.authority === 'server'
 u.path === '/shares/c$/file.txt'
 u.fsPath === '\\server\c$\folder\file.txt'
```

Using `Uri#path` to read a file (using fs-apis) would not be enough because parts of the path,
namely the server name, would be missing. Therefore `Uri#fsPath` exists - it's sugar to ease working
with URIs that represent files on disk (`file` scheme).
fsPath.title: fsPath

scheme.description:
scheme is the 'http' part of 'http://www.msft.com/some/path?query#fragment'.
The part before the first colon.
scheme.title: scheme

If it is a function, it will be invoked when rendering a line number and the return value will be rendered.
Otherwise, if it is a truey, line numbers will be rendered normally (equivalent of using an identity function).
Otherwise, line numbers will not be rendered.
Defaults to `on`.
lineNumbers.title: lineNumbers

lineNumbersMinChars.description:
Control the width of line numbers, by reserving horizontal space for rendering at least an amount of digits.
Defaults to 5.
lineNumbersMinChars.title: lineNumbersMinChars

links.description:
Enable detecting links and making them clickable.
Defaults to true.
links.title: links

matchBrackets.description:
Enable highlighting of matching brackets.
Defaults to 'always'.
matchBrackets.title: matchBrackets

maxTokenizationLineLength.description:
Lines above this length will not be tokenized for performance reasons.
Defaults to 20000.
maxTokenizationLineLength.title: maxTokenizationLineLength

minimap.description: Control the behavior and rendering of the minimap.
minimap.title: minimap

model.description: The initial model associated with this code editor.
model.title: model

mouseStyle.description:
Control the mouse pointer style, either 'text' or 'default' or 'copy'
Defaults to 'text'
mouseStyle.title: mouseStyle

mouseWheelScrollSensitivity.description:
A multiplier to be used on the `deltaX` and `deltaY` of mouse wheel scroll events.
Defaults to 1.
mouseWheelScrollSensitivity.title: mouseWheelScrollSensitivity

mouseWheelZoom.description:
Zoom the font in the editor when using the mouse wheel in combination with holding Ctrl.
Defaults to false.
mouseWheelZoom.title: mouseWheelZoom

multiCursorMergeOverlapping.description:
Merge overlapping selections.
Defaults to true
multiCursorMergeOverlapping.title: multiCursorMergeOverlapping

multiCursorModifier.description:
The modifier to be used to add multiple cursors with the mouse.
Defaults to 'alt'
multiCursorModifier.title: multiCursorModifier

multiCursorPaste.description:
Configure the behaviour when pasting a text with the line count equal to the cursor count.
Defaults to 'spread'.
multiCursorPaste.title: multiCursorPaste

occurrencesHighlight.description:
Enable semantic occurrences highlight.
Defaults to true.
occurrencesHighlight.title: occurrencesHighlight

overflowWidgetsDomNode.description:
Place overflow widgets inside an external DOM node.
Defaults to an internal DOM node.
overflowWidgetsDomNode.title: overflowWidgetsDomNode

overviewRulerBorder.description:
Controls if a border should be drawn around the overview ruler.
Defaults to `true`.
overviewRulerBorder.title: overviewRulerBorder

overviewRulerLanes.description:
The number of vertical lanes the overview ruler should render.
Defaults to 3.
overviewRulerLanes.title: overviewRulerLanes

padding.description: Controls the spacing around the editor.
padding.title: padding

peekWidgetDefaultFocus.description:
Controls whether to focus the inline editor in the peek widget by default.
Defaults to false.
peekWidgetDefaultFocus.title: peekWidgetDefaultFocus

quickSuggestions.description:
Enable quick suggestions (shadow suggestions)
Defaults to true.
quickSuggestions.title: quickSuggestions

quickSuggestionsDelay.description:
Quick suggestions show delay (in ms)
Defaults to 10 (ms)
quickSuggestionsDelay.title: quickSuggestionsDelay

readOnly.description:
Should the editor be read only.
Defaults to false.
readOnly.title: readOnly

renameOnType.description:
Rename matching regions on type.
Defaults to false.
renameOnType.title: renameOnType

renderControlCharacters.description:
Enable rendering of control characters.
Defaults to false.
renderControlCharacters.title: renderControlCharacters

renderFinalNewline.description:
Render last line number when the file ends with a newline.
Defaults to true.
renderFinalNewline.title: renderFinalNewline

renderIndentGuides.description:
Enable rendering of indent guides.
Defaults to true.
renderIndentGuides.title: renderIndentGuides

renderLineHighlight.description:
Enable rendering of current line highlight.
Defaults to all.
renderLineHighlight.title: renderLineHighlight

renderLineHighlightOnlyWhenFocus.description:
Control if the current line highlight should be rendered only the editor is focused.
Defaults to false.
renderLineHighlightOnlyWhenFocus.title: renderLineHighlightOnlyWhenFocus

renderValidationDecorations.description:
Should the editor render validation decorations.
Defaults to editable.
renderValidationDecorations.title: renderValidationDecorations

renderWhitespace.description:
Enable rendering of whitespace.
Defaults to none.
renderWhitespace.title: renderWhitespace

revealHorizontalRightPadding.description:
When revealing the cursor, a virtual padding (px) is added to the cursor, turning it into a rectangle.
This virtual padding ensures that the cursor gets revealed before hitting the edge of the viewport.
Defaults to 30 (px).
revealHorizontalRightPadding.title: revealHorizontalRightPadding

roundedSelection.description:
Render the editor selection with rounded borders.
Defaults to true.
roundedSelection.title: roundedSelection

rulers.description:
Render vertical lines at the specified columns.
Defaults to empty array.
rulers.title: rulers

scrollBeyondLastColumn.description:
Enable that scrolling can go beyond the last column by a number of columns.
Defaults to 5.
scrollBeyondLastColumn.title: scrollBeyondLastColumn

scrollBeyondLastLine.description:
Enable that scrolling can go one screen size after the last line.
Defaults to true.
scrollBeyondLastLine.title: scrollBeyondLastLine

scrollPredominantAxis.description:
Enable that the editor scrolls only the predominant axis. Prevents horizontal drift when scrolling vertically on a trackpad.
Defaults to true.
scrollPredominantAxis.title: scrollPredominantAxis

scrollbar.description: Control the behavior and rendering of the scrollbars.
scrollbar.title: scrollbar

selectOnLineNumbers.description:
Should the corresponding line be selected when clicking on the line number?
Defaults to true.
selectOnLineNumbers.title: selectOnLineNumbers

selectionClipboard.description:
Enable Linux primary clipboard.
Defaults to true.
selectionClipboard.title: selectionClipboard

selectionHighlight.description:
Enable selection highlight.
Defaults to true.
selectionHighlight.title: selectionHighlight

semanticHighlighting.enabled.description:
Controls whether the semanticHighlighting is shown for the languages that support it.
true: semanticHighlighting is enabled for all themes
false: semanticHighlighting is disabled for all themes
'configuredByTheme': semanticHighlighting is controlled by the current color theme's semanticHighlighting setting.
Defaults to 'byTheme'.
semanticHighlighting.enabled.title: semanticHighlighting.enabled

showFoldingControls.description:
Controls whether the fold actions in the gutter stay always visible or hide unless the mouse is over the gutter.
Defaults to 'mouseover'.
showFoldingControls.title: showFoldingControls

showUnused.description: Controls fading out of unused variables.
showUnused.title: showUnused

smoothScrolling.description:
Enable that the editor animates scrolling to a position.
Defaults to false.
smoothScrolling.title: smoothScrolling

stablePeek.description:
Keep peek editors open even when double clicking their content or when hitting `Escape`.
Defaults to false.
stablePeek.title: stablePeek

stopRenderingLineAfter.description:
Performance guard: Stop rendering a line after x characters.
Defaults to 10000.
Use -1 to never stop rendering
stopRenderingLineAfter.title: stopRenderingLineAfter

suggestFontSize.description:
The font size for the suggest widget.
Defaults to the editor font size.
suggestFontSize.title: suggestFontSize

suggestLineHeight.description:
The line height for the suggest widget.
Defaults to the editor line height.
suggestLineHeight.title: suggestLineHeight

suggestOnTriggerCharacters.description:
Enable the suggestion box to pop-up on trigger characters.
Defaults to true.
suggestOnTriggerCharacters.title: suggestOnTriggerCharacters

tabIndex.description: The `tabindex` property of the editor's textarea
tabIndex.title: tabIndex

tabSize.description:
The number of spaces a tab is equal to.
This setting is overridden based on the file contents when `detectIndentation` is on.
Defaults to 4.
tabSize.title: tabSize

theme.description:
Initial theme to be used for rendering.
The current out-of-the-box available themes are: 'vs' (default), 'vs-dark', 'hc-black'.
You can create custom themes via `monaco.editor.defineTheme`.
To switch a theme, use `monaco.editor.setTheme`
theme.title: theme

trimAutoWhitespace.description:
Remove trailing auto inserted whitespace.
Defaults to true.
trimAutoWhitespace.title: trimAutoWhitespace

unfoldOnClickAfterEndOfLine.description:
Controls whether clicking on the empty content after a folded line will unfold the line.
Defaults to false.
unfoldOnClickAfterEndOfLine.title: unfoldOnClickAfterEndOfLine

unusualLineTerminators.description:
Remove unusual line terminators like LINE SEPARATOR (LS), PARAGRAPH SEPARATOR (PS).
Defaults to 'prompt'.
unusualLineTerminators.title: unusualLineTerminators

useTabStops.description: Inserting and deleting whitespace follows tab stops.
useTabStops.title: useTabStops

value.description:
The initial value of the auto created model in the editor.
To not create automatically a model, use `model: null`.
value.title: value

wordBasedSuggestions.description:
Controls whether completions should be computed based on words in the document.
Defaults to true.
wordBasedSuggestions.title: wordBasedSuggestions

wordSeparators.description:
A string containing the word separators used when doing word navigation.
Defaults to `~!@#$%^&*()-=+[{]}\\|;:\'",.<>/?
wordSeparators.title: wordSeparators

wordWrap.description:
Control the wrapping of the editor.
When `wordWrap` = "off", the lines will never wrap.
When `wordWrap` = "on", the lines will wrap at the viewport width.
When `wordWrap` = "wordWrapColumn", the lines will wrap at `wordWrapColumn`.
When `wordWrap` = "bounded", the lines will wrap at min(viewport width, wordWrapColumn).
Defaults to "off".
wordWrap.title: wordWrap

wordWrapBreakAfterCharacters.description:
Configure word wrapping characters. A break will be introduced after these characters.
Defaults to ' \t})]?|/&.,;¢°′″‰℃、。｡､￠，．：；？！％・･ゝゞヽヾーァィゥェォッャュョヮヵヶぁぃぅぇぉっゃゅょゎゕゖㇰㇱㇲㇳㇴㇵㇶㇷㇸㇹㇺㇻㇼㇽㇾㇿ々〻ｧｨｩｪｫｬｭｮｯｰ”〉》」』】〕）］｝｣'.
wordWrapBreakAfterCharacters.title: wordWrapBreakAfterCharacters

wordWrapBreakBeforeCharacters.description:
Configure word wrapping characters. A break will be introduced before these characters.
Defaults to '([{‘“〈《「『【〔（［｛｢£¥＄￡￥+＋'.
wordWrapBreakBeforeCharacters.title: wordWrapBreakBeforeCharacters

wordWrapColumn.description:
Control the wrapping of the editor.
When `wordWrap` = "off", the lines will never wrap.
When `wordWrap` = "on", the lines will wrap at the viewport width.
When `wordWrap` = "wordWrapColumn", the lines will wrap at `wordWrapColumn`.
When `wordWrap` = "bounded", the lines will wrap at min(viewport width, wordWrapColumn).
Defaults to 80.
wordWrapColumn.title: wordWrapColumn

wordWrapMinified.description:
Force word wrapping when the text appears to be of a minified/generated file.
Defaults to true.
wordWrapMinified.title: wordWrapMinified

wrappingIndent.description:
Control indentation of wrapped lines. Can be: 'none', 'same', 'indent' or 'deepIndent'.
Defaults to 'same' in vscode and to 'none' in monaco-editor.
wrappingIndent.title: wrappingIndent

wrappingStrategy.description:
Controls the wrapping strategy to use.
Defaults to 'simple'.
wrappingStrategy.title: wrappingStrategy

filterGraceful.description: Enable graceful matching. Defaults to true.
filterGraceful.title: filterGraceful

insertMode.description: Overwrite word ends on accept. Default to false.
insertMode.title: insertMode

localityBonus.description: Favours words that appear close to the cursor.
localityBonus.title: localityBonus

maxVisibleSuggestions.description: Max suggestions to show in suggestions. Defaults to 12.
maxVisibleSuggestions.title: maxVisibleSuggestions

shareSuggestSelections.description: Enable using global storage for remembering suggestions.
shareSuggestSelections.title: shareSuggestSelections

showIcons.description: Enable or disable icons in suggestions. Defaults to true.
showIcons.title: showIcons

snippetsPreventQuickSuggestions.description: Prevent quick suggestions when a snippet is active. Defaults to true.
snippetsPreventQuickSuggestions.title: snippetsPreventQuickSuggestions

visible.description: Controls the visibility of the status bar at the bottom of the suggest widget.
visible.title: visible
